      "details": "On June 8, 2026, President Trump urged Israel and Iran to halt strikes after an exchange of attacks threatened to reignite war in the Middle East. This followed Iranian salvos in response to Israeli attacks on Hezbollah, an Iran-backed group. The conflict, dubbed Operation Epic Fury, had been ongoing for 100 days. Such geopolitical instability typically diverts consumer attention and creates economic uncertainty, leading to suppressed discretionary spending.",
